description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Full Time Apprentice to join West Kent Community Mental Health Team , providing an efficient and comprehensive administration support within the admin team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be a team player, with good communication and interpersonal skills, have the ability to prioritise your workload and work to agreed timescales. Also required is a flexible approach to your work and a professional attitude.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will provide a comprehensive administration service to members of the Community Mental Health team including minuting meetings, accessing patient records to send correspondence and make appointments, covering the switch board and reception, and typing letters and notes from doctors and other mental health professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will have knowledge of MS Office applications i.e. Word, Outlook, Excel and PowerPoint.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder would be required to work 37.5 hours per week&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For further information please contact Fiona Anderson Apprentice Lead on 07590 328593&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fiona Anderson, Telephone: 07590 328593&lt;/p&gt;
